data.name: Label4.Text
data.value: The data should be organized in a spreadsheet or text editor first, then copied to Windows Clipboard, then pasted into the Catalog Data Wizard. The data columns should be delimited by tabs and lines delimited by carriage returns.

data.name: Label8.Text
data.value: The data can be entered in any units. To change the units for the data you entered, you have two options: 1. To change one column, right click on the corresponding column in the top grid and choose the correct units. 2. To quickly change unit system (if you entered data in IP-units, for instance, quick the IP or SI buttons at the bottom. You can then fine tune individual columns.

data.name: Label7.Text
data.value: If the data you pasted is in the wrong order (columns), don't worry, you have two options: 1. To do a quick swap of columns, just click on the corresponding column in the top grid, you can select a target column there. 2. If the columns are completely wrong, click 'repair columns' to do a full repair.

data.name: Label6.Text
data.value: The results will differ for your component type, but will typically include a set of coefficients and parameters. In addition, if an E+ object is requested, the output will already be in the form ready for insertion in a user input (IDF) file. Some data such as component name and node names will have to be customized to match the rest of the IDF.
